docs.snippet: Collier, a 6-foot-5 center from the University of Texas, was selected by the Dallas Wings, which also picked Awak Kuier and Chelsea Dungee in the first round.
docs.lead_paragraph: Charli Collier, a center from the University of Texas, was selected No. 1 over all by the Dallas Wings in the W.N.B.A.’s virtual draft on Thursday, fulfilling the dream of her late father that she be the top pick. Collier, who is from Texas and was widely projected to be the first pick, averaged 19 points and 11.3 rebounds per game in the 2020-21 season.

headline.main: Charli Collier Is the No. 1 Pick in the W.N.B.A. Draft
headline.print_headline: Dallas Shops Local, Taking Texas Star With W.N.B.A.’s Top Pick
